# Claude Code's Workflow tool loads these orchestration scripts via `scriptPath`
# and rejects carriage-return (CR) control characters in the script body. On a
# Windows checkout, the default `core.autocrlf=true` rewrites the LF-clean git
# blobs to CRLF in the working tree, which makes the Workflow tool refuse to
# load them. Pin them to LF so a fresh clone stays loadable regardless of the
# user's autocrlf setting (the blobs are already LF, so this only constrains the
# working tree).
*.workflow.js text eol=lf
